# haproxy patch for ocr.rotko.net
# Applied via deploy/apply-haproxy.py to the haproxy.cfg on every
# anycast peer (bkk06, bkk07, bkk08 hosts AND their LXC haproxies).
#
# Three insertion points:

# 1. In `frontend ssl-frontend`, after the astrolabe ACL:
#       acl is_ocr hdr_end(host) -i ocr.rotko.net
# and after the astrolabe use_backend:
#       use_backend ocr-backend if is_ocr

# 2. Add the backend block, after the astrolabe backend block:
#
#       # OCR Online (ocr.rotko.net)
#       backend ocr-backend
#           mode http
#           balance leastconn
#           # nginx sets framing per location (SPA=SAMEORIGIN,
#           # embed=*); signal the ssl-frontend NOT to override
#           # X-Frame-Options on ocr-backend responses.
#           http-request set-var(txn.skip_xfo) bool(true)
#           option httpchk
#           http-check send meth GET uri /__health hdr Host ocr.rotko.net
#           http-check expect status 200
#           http-response set-header X-Served-By "ocr-rotko-net"
#           server bkk07-ocr 192.168.77.92:80 check inter 5s fall 3 rise 2
#           server bkk08-ocr 192.168.78.92:80 check inter 5s fall 3 rise 2

# 3. Modify the global ssl-frontend X-Frame-Options line:
#   FROM:
#       http-response set-header X-Frame-Options "DENY"
#   TO:
#       http-response set-header X-Frame-Options "DENY" if !{ var(txn.skip_xfo) -m bool }
